	Posts: 1854</font></td>
	
	<td bgcolor="#F7F7F7" width="100%" valign="top">
	<font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial"> <b>Testing Heal aggro</b></font>
	<p><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial">I am pondering how to effectively test heal aggro - and as such I am asking for ideas.<br />
<br />
Some of the questions I would like to end up answering are:<br />
<br />
- Do different direct heals have intrinsic different aggro? <br />
Example: Does healing 1500 hp with SR have the same aggro as healing 1500 hp with SL - or with CH? All other things being equal.<br />
<br />
- Is 1 large heal = 2 smaller heals in aggro?<br />
Example: Tank missing 2k. Is 2x SR for 2k each the same aggro as 1x SL for 4k?<br />
<br />
- Does the aggro depend on the number of hp healed if the same spell is used? (all other things being equal)<br />
Example: Is healing a tank from 7k to 10k equal aggro to healing the same tank from 8k to 10k.l<br />
<br />
- Does a crit heal aggro more than a non crit? <br />
-- A) If they heal an equal amount despite the crit<br />
-- B) If the crit actually heals for more<br />
<br />
-- If the healed amount matters for aggro - does the part from focus items add aggro or not? <br />
<br />
If anyone has any input to how I should go about testing this (weak mobs with "good" aggro behaviour for example) then I would love to hear so. Mind - I am not asking for guessing as to the answers to the above questions - I am looking to test and provide accurate data.</font></p>
	
	<p><p><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial">__________________<br>
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=4264" target="_blank">Mikar of the Nexus</a><br />
