<table bgcolor="#FFFFFF" width="95%" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0"><tr><td width="10"><img width="10" height="1" src="images/space.gif" alt=""></td><td width="100%"><!-- spacer -->

<table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" bgcolor=""  width="95%" align="center"><tr><td>
<table cellpadding="4" cellspacing="1" border="0"  width="100%">
<tr>
	<td bgcolor="#F7F7F7" width="175" valign="top" nowrap>
	<a name="post202091"></a>
	
	<font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial"><b>JanSorensen</b></font><br>
	<font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">Fighting misinformation</font><br>
	<p>
	<font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">Registered: Feb 2000<br>
	Location: Denmark<br>
	Posts: 1854</font></td>
	
	<td bgcolor="#F7F7F7" width="100%" valign="top">
	<font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial"> <b></b></font>
	<p><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial">Initial test (failed horribly)<br />
<br />
I just tried my first idea. I had a 65 cleric + a 50 necro to test with.<br />
<br />
I decided to use a non-kos mob - Delin Ironblend in Butcherblock. Green to 65, light blue to 50 (if that matters in any way).<br />
<br />
Necro used Mana stone to drop some health.<br />
Necro cast Shock of Poison (160 dd) to aggro.<br />
Cleric cast SR on necro before mob was in camp.<br />
Check if cleric got aggro.<br />
Cleric casts Atone <br />
<br />
Result: <br />
- 2196 and 1664 respectively healed = aggro on cleric.<br />
<br />
Then I ran into problems though - as the next many tests left the cleric non-kos after healing (and hence obviously aggro didnt shift). So, it seems the good old "heals sometimes dont give ANY aggro" bug is still alive and well - atleast in this particular case.<br />
<br />
I then tried to change the order a little - thinking that it might atleast be so that it was only when not already aggro that heals didnt give +aggro.<br />
<br />
Clr: MoKings<br />
Nec: Shock of Poison (= necro on top of aggro list)<br />
Clr: SR (actually multiple SR) untill aggro<br />
<br />
But, the results varied wildly<br />
- 858 <br />
- 148, 105, 90<br />
- 328, 75, 118, 220, 291, 153, 1721<br />
- 652, 1060, 705<br />
were the SR "chains" it took to get the mob to turn. In all cases the cleric was closer to the mob than the necro when casting - and in no case did the necro move out of melee range.<br />
<br />
So, it seems the "no +aggro" from heals also apply here. Either that - or the aggro is much more random that I would have thought.<br />
<br />
<br />
Anyway - back to the drawing board - ideas are very welcome.</font></p>
	
	<p><p><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial">__________________<br>
