<tr>
	<td bgcolor="#F7F7F7" width="175" valign="top" nowrap>
	<a name="post202105"></a>
	
	<font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial"><b>Kahlia</b></font><br>
	<font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">Venerable</font><br>
	<p>
	<font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">Registered: Apr 2001<br>
	Location: <br>
	Posts: 584</font></td>
	
	<td bgcolor="#F7F7F7" width="100%" valign="top">
	<font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial"> <b></b></font>
	<p><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial">I'd be very interested to see more data on this.  I've often wondered about it myself.  <br />
<br />
The last patch I remember talking specifics about heal agro was in velious, and they implied that it didn't matter what spell it was. But clearly at the beginning of PoP a druid could ICH for the same amount as our SR and we would get aggro, not them.<br />
<br />
So there is definately a way for SOE to apply aggro based on the spell itself, regardless of amount healed.  The question is are they utilizing it, and if so, where are they utilizing it.<br />
<br />
Found some quotes for us:<br />
<br />
<a href="http://eq.crgaming.com/viewarticle.asp?Article=3249" target="_blank">http://eq.crgaming.com/viewarticle.asp?Article=3249</a><br />
"There is a cap on the amount of hate that can be awarded for any particular heal spell.  For a target below level 51, no heal spell can generate more than 800 hate, regardless of the number of hitpoints healed.  For targets level 51 or above, the cap is higher, but does not approach the total hitpoints of a fully buffed warrior." Patch Message, 2/25/01<br />
<br />
<a href="http://eq.crgaming.com/viewarticle.asp?Article=3252" target="_blank">http://eq.crgaming.com/viewarticle.asp?Article=3252</a><br />
"Actually, you are incorrect.  The maximum healing of the spell is never looked at, only the points actually healed." Absor, 2/27/01<br />
<br />
<a href="http://eq.crgaming.com/viewarticle.asp?Article=3275" target="_blank">http://eq.crgaming.com/viewarticle.asp?Article=3275</a><br />
"Hate from heals is also now calculated at a lesser number than the number of hitpoints healed.  Previously, healing one hitpoint would cause one point of hate.  Now, healing 3 hitpoints will cause 2 points of hate." Patch Message, 3/6/01<br />
<br />
<a href="http://eq.crgaming.com/viewarticle.asp?Article=4972" target="_blank">http://eq.crgaming.com/viewarticle.asp?Article=4972</a><br />
"NPCs will now notice Druid and Shaman Percentage Heal spells in a manner similar to traditional healing spells." Patch Message, 1/15/03</font></p>
	
	<p><p><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial">__________________<br>
